Meat pies are a type of pie that can be obtained by baking an uncooked meat pie on a cooking range, requiring level 20 Cooking and granting 110 experience when successful. Players may burn the pie while baking one, resulting in a burnt pie; the burn rate while cooking these will decrease as players reach higher Cooking levels. It will stop burning entirely at Cooking level 54 on ranges. Alternatively, casting the Bake Pie spell from the lunar spellbook guarantees successful baking of all pies.

Meat pie heals 12 Hitpoints in total, 2 bites each healing 6. After eating it, a pie dish will remain.

Romily Weaklax, in the Cooks' Guild, may ask the player for a meat pie, paying 96 coins each. They do not have to be made by the player to get the reward.

Meat pies can be purchased from the Cooks' Guild Pie Shop for 15 coins, Forester's Arms pub in Seers' Village for 16 coins, or West Ardougne General Store for 18 coins

Steps
1. Use a pastry dough on a pie dish to make a pie shell
2. Use cooked meat on the pie shell to make an uncooked meat pie
3. Cook the uncooked meat pie on a range to finish a meat pie
